Today I had an absolutely horrendous experience, so much so that it's prompted me to write a rare review. This is the kind of behavior that makes me condemn America as a third-rate country. I sat down in a chair for a few minutes with my small service dog. I finished my pastry and got up to grab my coat. I set my dog on the chair and at that moment, one of the employees storms by me in a fury and unleashes on me like a parent scolding a child. This woman looked disheveled to say the least.

"Get your dog off that chair, people have to sit there!!" she aggressively yelled at me. I'm sorry, but this sort of abuse is not only unwarranted in a hospitality industry, it doesn't belong in civil society. She might talk to her kids or husband like that, but she has no right to scold paying customers in public.

Instead of treating me with respect, this woman unleashes and then  storms past me into a room labeled "employees" and SLAMS the doors.

I have been to Starbucks and NUMEROUS cafes all over the city and the world with my dog and I have never experienced such barbaric hostility. In fact, most of these places offer a treat to my dog and many of them welcome the small animal a seat.

And by the looks of it in this cafe, a small animal is probably among the least hygienic concerns. I often see homeless and obvious drug addicts hanging out here.

I have no desire to return to such a place that welcomes this kind of hostility, disrespect, and lowlife behavior from its employees.

This woman could have very well approached me in a polite and intelligent manner, but she did not. This incident happened on Saturday March 12, 2022 around 12 PM. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Devin Zweifel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117730289559902008385/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GisY5MOtjc_RBn1FAKA-5J8UFzMvXreQlcHokFb89w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Great coffee! However, in my estimation, an establishment’s true quality can be determined by the cleanliness of its restroom. He who is faithful in what is least is faithful in much. Granted, you may argue, ‘but we had not time for it!’ Understandable, but not excusable. Thank you for the beverage but you need to work on your core values Mr. Nero. By the way, my understanding of the issue, not being an expert business person, is that your employees are overworked and stressed. I will not give names or a description of these highly favored workers because they are not to be blamed for not having the resources to clean the restroom. You are dear manager. Take responsibility or choose a different course in life. A suggestion from a random guy passing through town. Today I had an absolutely horrendous experience, so much so that it's prompted me to write a rare review. This is the kind of behavior that makes me condemn America as a third-rate country. I sat down in a chair for a few minutes with my small service dog. I finished my pastry and got up to grab my coat. I set my dog on the chair and at that moment, one of the employees storms by me in a fury and unleashes on me like a parent scolding a child. This woman looked disheveled to say the least.

"Get your dog off that chair, people have to sit there!!" she aggressively yelled at me. I'm sorry, but this sort of abuse is not only unwarranted in a hospitality industry, it doesn't belong in civil society. She might talk to her kids or husband like that, but she has no right to scold paying customers in public.

Instead of treating me with respect, this woman unleashes and then  storms past me into a room labeled "employees" and SLAMS the doors.

I have been to Starbucks and NUMEROUS cafes all over the city and the world with my dog and I have never experienced such barbaric hostility. In fact, most of these places offer a treat to my dog and many of them welcome the small animal a seat.

And by the looks of it in this cafe, a small animal is probably among the least hygienic concerns. I often see homeless and obvious drug addicts hanging out here.

I have no desire to return to such a place that welcomes this kind of hostility, disrespect, and lowlife behavior from its employees.

This woman could have very well approached me in a polite and intelligent manner, but she did not. This incident happened on Saturday March 12, 2022 around 12 PM. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Devin Zweifel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117730289559902008385/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GisY5MOtjc_RBn1FAKA-5J8UFzMvXreQlcHokFb89w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Great coffee! However, in my estimation, an establishment’s true quality can be determined by the cleanliness of its restroom. He who is faithful in what is least is faithful in much. Granted, you may argue, ‘but we had not time for it!’ Understandable, but not excusable. Thank you for the beverage but you need to work on your core values Mr. Nero. By the way, my understanding of the issue, not being an expert business person, is that your employees are overworked and stressed. I will not give names or a description of these highly favored workers because they are not to be blamed for not having the resources to clean the restroom. You are dear manager. Take responsibility or choose a different course in life. A suggestion from a random guy passing through town. Today I had an absolutely horrendous experience, so much so that it's prompted me to write a rare review. This is the kind of behavior that makes me condemn America as a third-rate country. I sat down in a chair for a few minutes with my small service dog. I finished my pastry and got up to grab my coat. I set my dog on the chair and at that moment, one of the employees storms by me in a fury and unleashes on me like a parent scolding a child. This woman looked disheveled to say the least.

"Get your dog off that chair, people have to sit there!!" she aggressively yelled at me. I'm sorry, but this sort of abuse is not only unwarranted in a hospitality industry, it doesn't belong in civil society. She might talk to her kids or husband like that, but she has no right to scold paying customers in public.

Instead of treating me with respect, this woman unleashes and then  storms past me into a room labeled "employees" and SLAMS the doors.

I have been to Starbucks and NUMEROUS cafes all over the city and the world with my dog and I have never experienced such barbaric hostility. In fact, most of these places offer a treat to my dog and many of them welcome the small animal a seat.

And by the looks of it in this cafe, a small animal is probably among the least hygienic concerns. I often see homeless and obvious drug addicts hanging out here.

I have no desire to return to such a place that welcomes this kind of hostility, disrespect, and lowlife behavior from its employees.

This woman could have very well approached me in a polite and intelligent manner, but she did not. This incident happened on Saturday March 12, 2022 around 12 PM. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Devin Zweifel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117730289559902008385/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GisY5MOtjc_RBn1FAKA-5J8UFzMvXreQlcHokFb89w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Great coffee! However, in my estimation, an establishment’s true quality can be determined by the cleanliness of its restroom. He who is faithful in what is least is faithful in much. Granted, you may argue, ‘but we had not time for it!’ Understandable, but not excusable. Thank you for the beverage but you need to work on your core values Mr. Nero. By the way, my understanding of the issue, not being an expert business person, is that your employees are overworked and stressed. I will not give names or a description of these highly favored workers because they are not to be blamed for not having the resources to clean the restroom. You are dear manager. Take responsibility or choose a different course in life. A suggestion from a random guy passing through town. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Brian Denzer', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105623533435135442233/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgkthDjamdhYE3JPztzkcrTOxe3kNgLdK4K0ZJM_Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "A magical experience! I know - extreme hyperbole for coffee, right? I'd never been here before. I was in the neighborhood and wanted iced coffee. I chose the locally-owned shop over the big national chain nearby. A cheerful greeting set the tone. I don't get that from the big chain. Everyone there always seems run down, punching a clock. Then, after placing an order for iced coffee, I was patiently provided a range of milk offerings, and - here comes the magical part - I was asked what color I like my iced coffee to be - if I like the color to change. Why, yes! Thank you for asking! I like my iced coffee to be creamy, to take the edge off the coffee acidity. Isn't that how it always should be? Most places just top off a cup with ice and then coffee, and drizzle in a few molecules of milk. In my lifetime, I can't recall any other coffee shop that has asked this particular question about coffee color, and it was perfectly asked. I don't know about the rest of you, but the rest of you, but these little details make the difference. I didn:t stay to dine, but I noticed that guest diners' food was plated nicely, and everything looked clean and well organized. These are all signs of good ownership, and good management, focused on cultivating a happy and loyal repeat customer experience. Again, however mundane my order was, it was still a magical experience. No, I have no idea who the owners are.
